    "locked": false,
    "title": "Educational Hopper Matmul level_07 Warp Specialization Fix",
    "user": {
      "login": "tspeterkim",
      "id": 6720887,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY3MjA4ODc=",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6720887?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/tspeterkim",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tspeterkim/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "The current `level_07` kernel, which is meant to improve perf through work partitioning, regresses compared to `level_06`.\r\n\r\n`level_06` output:\r\n```\r\nAvg Kernel execution time: 775.35 us\r\nAchieved performance: 177.261 TFLOPs\r\n```\r\n\r\n`level_07` output:\r\n```\r\nAvg Kernel execution time: 797.44 us\r\nAchieved performance: 172.35 TFLOPs\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe current warp specialization implementation only overlaps the next tile’s TMA load with the current tile’s MMA compute (doing nothing different from the previous double buffering in `level_06`). Ideally, the end of current compute should signal the next load to begin, allowing multiple TMA transfers to pipeline across tiles.\r\n\r\nHowever, currently there is only a single shared barrier for both producer and consumer warpgroups, where only one TMA load can be in-flight at a time.\r\n\r\nHere, I allocate more barriers and use an independent for loop per warpgroup. This allows more opportunities for load-compute overlap, and restores the presumably intended benefits of warp specialization.\r\n\r\nFixed `level_07 `output:\r\n```\r\nAvg Kernel execution time: 542.029 us\r\nAchieved performance: 253.564 TFLOPs\r\n```",
